# Testing (Realms Android)

Tests run on **Robolectric** (SDK 34), **JUnit 4**, **JVM only** (no instrumented tests).

## Layout

```
app/src/test/kotlin/com/realmsoffate/game/
├── data/
│   └── TagParserTest.kt              — tokenizer + segment parser
└── game/
    ├── ApplyParsedIntegrationTest.kt — turn pipeline / reducers
    ├── MerchantHandlerTest.kt
    ├── RestHandlerTest.kt
    ├── SaveServiceTest.kt
    ├── ProgressionHandlerTest.kt
    ├── GameStateFixture.kt           — character(), baseState(), viewModelWithState()
    └── ParsedReplyBuilder.kt        — ParsedReply builders
```

## When to write tests

| Changed | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Reducer / `applyParsed` behavior | Extend **`ApplyParsedIntegrationTest`** + `ParsedReplyBuilder` |
| Tag parsing / tokenizer | Extend **`TagParserTest`** |
| Merchant / Rest / Save / Progression handlers | Extend that handler’s test class |
| Bug in game logic | Add a **regression** test |
| UI-only, copy, cosmetics | Usually **no** new test |

## Reducer-style example

```kotlin
@Test fun `your test name`() {
    val vm = viewModelWithState(baseState(
        character = character(hp = 50, maxHp = 100)
    ))
    val parsed = ParsedReplyBuilder()
        .heal(20)
        .narration("You feel restored.")
        .build()

    vm.applyParsed(parsed, diceResult = null)

    val state = vm.readUiState()
    assertEquals(70, state.character.hp)
}
```

## Tag parser example

```kotlin
@Test fun `your test name`() {
    val segments = tokenize("[NPC_DIALOG:merchant]\"Fresh wares!\"/[NPC_DIALOG]")
    assertEquals(1, segments.size)
    assertEquals(SegmentType.NPC_DIALOG, segments[0].type)
    assertEquals("merchant", segments[0].speaker)
}
```

## Commands

```bash
gradle test
gradle test --tests "com.realmsoffate.game.data.TagParserTest"
gradle test --tests "com.realmsoffate.game.game.ApplyParsedIntegrationTest"
```

Full-suite runs apply after multi-area changes — see **`task-workflow.mdc`**.
